Anton Frans Koenraads , a 39-year-old teacher in Delft, the hometown of Johannes Vermeer, wrote about how the war in the Netherlands ended on May 5, 1945.
But Koenraads is among those who are slow to trust that the war is really over.
On this page of his diary, Anton Frans Koenraads, describes the liberation of Delft on May 6, 1945.
In it, I’ve tried to convey what has been on my mind during these recent months of the war.
I’ve had the painful privilege of having experienced an ‘all-out war.’ That is behind us now.